<subSubSection pageId="75" pageNumber="76" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="75.[151,1437,1628,2015]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1737,1763]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<specimenCount box="[377,518,1736,1763]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" type="generic">5 specimens</specimenCount>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[591,726,1736,1762]" name="Madagascar" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
reported as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Pillai" baseAuthorityYear="1957" box="[871,1141,1736,1762]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Metatiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevidactylus">
<emphasis box="[871,1141,1736,1762]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Metatiron brevidactylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ledoyer, M." box="[1188,1365,1736,1763]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" pagination="1 - 150" refId="ref49813" refString="Ledoyer, M. (1979) Les gammariens de la pente externe du grand recif de Tulear (Madagascar) (Crustacea Amphipoda). Memorie di Museo di Storia Naturale Verona, 2 (2), 1 - 150." type="journal article" year="1979">Ledoyer (1979)</bibRefCitation>
differ in many points from 
<bibRefCitation author="Pillai, N. K." box="[397,559,1772,1799]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" pagination="29 - 68" refId="ref50030" refString="Pillai, N. K. (1957) Pelagic Crustacea of Travancore. III. Amphipoda. Bulletin of the Central Research Institute of University of Travancore, 5, 29 - 68." type="journal article" year="1957">Pillai’s (1957)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Rabindranath, P." box="[619,872,1772,1799]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" pagination="84 - 97" refId="ref50147" refString="Rabindranath, P. (1972) Three species of gammaridean Amphipoda (Crustacea) from the Trivandrum Coast, India. Zoologischer Anzeiger, 188, 84 - 97." type="journal article" year="1972">Rabindranath’s (1972)</bibRefCitation>
descriptions. The specimens appear to belong in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Just" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,257,1809,1834]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Minitiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,257,1809,1834]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Minitiron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on account of the strongly curved basis of gnathopod 1, but description and illustrations lack necessary additional evidence, e.g. the 
<typeStatus box="[442,490,1845,1871]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">type</typeStatus>
of spine-setae on maxilla 1 outer plate. Hence, I do not feel the species is sufficiently well defined to propose a new name for it. It is removed to 
<taxonomicName box="[815,961,1881,1907]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Minitiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[815,921,1881,1906]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Minitiron</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
pending further studies.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="75.[151,1437,1628,2015]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<bibRefCitation author="Pillai, N. K." box="[199,340,1916,1943]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" pagination="29 - 68" refId="ref50030" refString="Pillai, N. K. (1957) Pelagic Crustacea of Travancore. III. Amphipoda. Bulletin of the Central Research Institute of University of Travancore, 5, 29 - 68." type="journal article" year="1957">Pillai (1957)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Rabindranath, P." box="[396,629,1916,1943]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" pagination="84 - 97" refId="ref50147" refString="Rabindranath, P. (1972) Three species of gammaridean Amphipoda (Crustacea) from the Trivandrum Coast, India. Zoologischer Anzeiger, 188, 84 - 97." type="journal article" year="1972">Rabindranath (1972)</bibRefCitation>
both mention that while males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Pillai" baseAuthorityYear="1957" box="[1017,1286,1916,1942]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Metatiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevidactylus">
<emphasis box="[1017,1286,1916,1942]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Metatiron brevidactylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a vestigial inner plate without setae on maxilla 1, females of the species have a more developed plate with a few terminal setae.
</paragraph>
